#  MEMS-Based Home Automation Using Bulb

This project controls a *bulb automatically* using a *MEMS accelerometer sensor* and *Arduino UNO*.  
When the sensor tilts, the Arduino reads the motion and activates a *relay module* to switch the bulb *ON or OFF*.

---

##  Working:
- MEMS sensor detects tilt/motion. 
- Arduino reads sensor values.  
- Relay turns the bulb ON/OFF based on tilt direction.  

---

##  Components:
- Arduino UNO. 
- MEMS Sensor (ADXL335 / MPU6050).  
- Relay Module  
- Bulb.
- Jumper Wires.
